        description: "The Lyon — Montélimar route takes the Autoroute du Soleil (A7) through the Rhône Valley. 160 km apart, the two cities are linked by one of France's busiest motorway corridors. Your TaxiNeo driver takes you directly from Lyon to the nougat capital, gateway to Provence.",
        routeDescription: "The route takes the A7 (Autoroute du Soleil) from Lyon heading south, passing through Vienne, Saint-Rambert-d'Albon, Tain-l'Hermitage and Valence before reaching Montélimar. The journey follows the Rhône offering panoramic views of the Côtes du Rhône vineyards with the Vercors as a backdrop.",
        introduction: "Montélimar, nicknamed the 'Gateway to Provence', is a characterful Drôme town famous worldwide for its artisanal nougat. Located at the confluence of the Rhône and Roubion rivers, it marks the transition between the northern Rhône Valley and the sun-drenched landscapes of Provence. A taxi from Lyon is ideal for food lovers heading to the historic nougat shops in the old town, travellers en route to the Ardèche gorges or Mont Ventoux, and professionals with meetings in the Montélimar business district. The Autoroute du Soleil (A7) linking the two cities is one of France's busiest roads, especially in summer during major holiday departures. This is why a TaxiNeo taxi, with its guaranteed fixed fare, is a comfortable and stress-free alternative to driving on this often-congested route. Your professional driver knows the best times to avoid traffic jams and can take alternative routes via the historic N7 road if needed.",
