        introduction: "Geneva, a global city nestled at the tip of Lake Geneva, is one of the world's most important diplomatic and financial centres. European headquarters of the United Nations, CERN, WHO, the International Red Cross and hundreds of non-governmental organisations, Calvin's city attracts thousands of professional travellers every week. A taxi from Lyon is the most comfortable and flexible way to connect these two metropolises, whether for a diplomatic mission, a conference at the Palais des Nations, a visit to CERN, or a tourist stay on the shores of Lake Geneva. Many travellers arrive by TGV or by air at Lyon-Saint Exupéry airport and need a reliable transfer to Geneva. TaxiNeo offers a door-to-door service with a guaranteed fixed fare including French tolls, with no surprises at the border. Our drivers are perfectly familiar with the Bardonnex customs procedures and the specifics of Geneva traffic.",
